volume.name: Injustice: Gods Among Us Year Five

description:
THE DARK TOWER STANDS

At last, the stage is set for the final battle! When the Tower of Trophaeum finally takes its true form, only one competition is left: a winnertakeall Parts War with Ikki and Ringo on one side, and Sora and Rika on the other! And nothing less than the fate of the world may be at stake…

Note: The digital edition (6/14/2016) for this volume was released before the print edition.
name: The Dark Tower Stands

description:
Gen Urobuchi and Shinjiro’s manga adaptation of Type-Moon’s hit anime and novel series continues! As the Fourth Holy Grail War rages, seven magi and their summoned heroes from history battle to the death to claim the Grail and have their wishes granted! The first conflict of the war begins with Saber and Lancer crossing blades!

The manga adaptation of Type-Moon’s hit anime and novel series!
name: Volume 2

description:
The Risks of Playing God

In the midst of an intensifying war, the government has decided that relying on Stigmata alone to determine Pandoras is no longer enough. Enter the "Evolution Pandora Project"--an experimental operation that seeks to create Pandora by implanting Stigmata into humans who are born with little to none of their own. Will these man-made warriors prove an asset alongside their natural Pandora sisters, or will the E-Pandora Project unleash a power greater than anyone can control?
name: Vol. 9-10

description:
Aoi still secretly pines for Shusei’s affection but constantly worries that revealing her feelings to him will bring their living situation to an end. Meanwhile, a new neighbor moves into Aoi and Shusei’s building—and it’s a student from their high school! Will this new resident bring big changes to Aoi and Shusei’s secret cohabitation?

Note: The digital edition (6/14/2016) for this volume was released before the print edition.
name: Boy Next Door

description:
There Is No Reset Button

Call it skill or dumb luck, but Mikami Shigeru has defeated his first real opponent in NOT ALIVE. With the help of his gaming avatar, Amamiya Kyouka, they have evaded the game's harsh punishment and are able to climb the ranks. However, now is not the time to celebrate. Kyouka reveals that the game is not just a fight for your life, but those who clear it are rewarded with anything their hearts desire.

Chapter 6 - 10.
name: Volume 2

description:
The new series from the legendary creator of Oh My Goddess!Hatsune Takanashi is a girl of simple tastes. Curry and friends are among her favorite things, but more than anything, pudding is her true love in life. She’s begun her new high school life at Kitsuka Academy, an all-girl boarding school high atop a mountain, and is looking forward to making new friends and eating some great food. Hatsune is guaranteed to have new and exciting experiences, but with a grade-schooler house mother, a mean rival who uses fermented soybeans as her weapon of choice, and a foreign exchange student who doesn’t seem to understand how clothes work, her new school life is sure to be interesting …

Note: The digital edition (6/14/2016) for this volume was released before the print edition.
name: Volume 2

description:
PERSONA Q: A NEW VIEW

Yasoinaba’s very own Investigation Team are back in action in a new adventure based on the critically acclaimed Persona Q series! While enjoying Yasogami High’s cultural festival, the Team suddenly hears the ringing of a mysterious bell and a bizarre, new exhibit appears at the festival. Inside this exhibit is a most curious maze—one that will take them on a wondrous and treacherous journey. And as they explore this labyrinth, they’ll meet new foes and maybe even some new allies from the Persona universe…THE MANGA OF THE HIT VIDEO GAME PERSONA Q!

Note: The digital edition (6/14/2016) for this volume was released before the print edition.
name: Volume 2

volume.name: Persona Q: Shadow of the Labyrinth Side: P4

description:
When Blood Starts To Boil

Kuro has never been the most enthusiastic of vampires, preferring to eat chips and lounge about rather than combat Tsubaki and his servants. But something changed after Lawless appeared, and now Kuro's past is catching up with him faster than he and Mahiru can possibly outrun it. Is the bond between Servamp and Eve enough to overcome this newest trial, or has the unlikeliest of duos finally met their match...?

description:
Jake Roth returns home after the events of ACTIONVERSE just in time to face a new extrahuman threat that’s menacing the streets of Philadelphia. And as dangerous as an eight year old girl who can control minds might be… wait until you meet her mother! Meanwhile, the ETF is working night and day to neutralize the growing extrahuman threat. Could they be closing in on Jake?
